<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870204-0104 </DOCNO><HL> Fletcher Buys StakeIn Vancouver FirmFor $506.6 Million</HL><DD> 02/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> T.BCFTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)PULP, PAPER, PACKAGING (ALL TYPES) (PUL) </IN><DATELINE> VANCOUVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Fletcher Challenge Ltd. of New Zealand agreed to pay $506.6 million (Canadian) for a 47% stake in British Columbia Forest Products Ltd., according to the Canadian firm.    British Columbia Forest added that Fletcher Challenge, a holding company, doesn't intend to boost the stake past 49%. The stock purchases, at $19 a share, include 6.3 million common shares from the British Columbia Forest treasury and 20.4 million shares from Gordon Capital Corp., a Toronto securities firm. The purchases are subject to regulatory approval and &quot;certain customary conditions,&quot; British Columbia Forest said.    British Columbia Forest said it plans to use the $120 million that it received from Fletcher Challenge to reduce long-term debt and to &quot;move ahead with plans for further growth and development of its business.&quot;    Fletcher Challenge also owns a 94% interest in another major forest products company based here, Crown Forest Industries Ltd. British Columbia Forest said it has been informed that Fletcher Challenge intends to keep the two holdings separate. </TEXT></DOC>